(f)Generally excludes loans under payment deferral programs offered
in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. Refer to Consumer Credit
Portfolio on pages 114-116 for further information on consumer
payment assistance activity. Includes loans to customers that have
exited COVID-19 payment deferral programs and are 90 or more
days past due, predominantly all of which were also at least 150
days past due and therefore considered collateral-dependent.
Collateral-dependent loans are charged down to the lower of
amortized cost or fair value of the underlying collateral less costs
to sell.
