The Federal Reserve’s TLAC rule requires the U.S.
GSIB top-tier holding companies, including the Firm, to
maintain minimum levels of external TLAC and eligible
long-term debt.
The minimum external TLAC and the minimum level of
eligible long-term debt requirements are shown below:
(a) RWA is the greater of Standardized and Advanced compared to their
respective minimum capital ratios.
Failure to maintain TLAC equal to or in excess of the
regulatory minimum plus applicable buffers will result in
limitations to the amount of capital that the Firm may
distribute, such as through dividends and common
share repurchases.
