JPMorgan Chase & Co./2020 Form 10-K 121
Management’ s discussion and analysis
Wholesale assistance
In March 2020, the Firm began providing assistance to
clients in response to the COVID-19 pandemic,
predominantly in the form of payment deferrals and
covenant modifications.
As of December 31, 2020, the Firm had approximately
$1.6 billion of retained loans still under payment
deferral, which has decreased approximately $4.6 billion
from the third quarter, and $15.1 billion from the second
quarter. Predominantly all clients that exited deferral are
current orhave paid down their loans, and the Firm has not
experienced significant new payment deferral requests.
The Firm continues to monitor the credit risk associated
with loans subject to deferrals throughout the deferral
period and on an ongoing basis after the borrowers are
required to resume making regularly scheduled
payments and considers expected losses of principal
and accrued interest on these loans in its allowance for
credit losses.
 
