Loan modifications
Certain loan modifications are considered to be TDRs as they provide various concessions to borrowers who are
experiencing financial difficulty. Loans with short-term or other insignificant modifications that are not considered
concessions are not TDRs nor are loans for which the Firm has elected to apply the option to suspend the application of
accounting guidance for TDRs as provided by the CARES Act and extended by the Consolidated Appropriations Act. The
carrying value of TDRs was $954 million and $501 million as of December 31, 2020 and 2019, respectively. The carrying
value of new TDRs was $734 million, $407 million and $718 million for the years ended December 31, 2020, 2019 and
2018, respectively. The impact of these modifications, as well as new TDRs, were not material to the Firm for the years
ended December 31, 2020, 2019 and 2018.(a)
